# Cost-effectiveness of carbapenemase detection in adult ICUs in Chile: Micro-costing and interrupted time series evidence from the GAIHN-AR initiative, 2022–2025

**Year:** 2026  
**Funder:** Center for Disease Control, US

## Overview

This repository contains the analytical materials for the study:

**Cost-effectiveness of carbapenemase detection in adult ICUs in Chile: Micro-costing and interrupted time series evidence from the GAIHN-AR initiative, 2022–2025**

The repository includes code and templates used to estimate the cost-effectiveness of carbapenemase detection in adult intensive care units (ICUs) in Chile, drawing on micro-costing and interrupted time series (ITS) analyses conducted within the GAIHN-AR initiative.

## Contents

- **Code used for cost-effectiveness analysis**  
  Scripts for data cleaning, parameter estimation, costing, sensitivity analyses, and cost-effectiveness modelling.

- **Template for micro-costing and resource utilisation**  
  Structured template used to collect and standardise data on resource use, unit costs, and implementation inputs.

